y Global revises portfolio, adding Infosys, HCL Tech, Indus Towers, SRF; exits Mphasis, Sun Pharma, Gravita.\nIt turns marginally overweight on IT sector, citing attractive valuations post AI sell-off; sees 6.5-18.3% return potential.","url":"https://www.livemint.com/market/stock-market-news/it-sector-valuations-turn-attractive-after-ai-sell-off-emkay-adds-infosys-hcl-tech-exits-mphasis-in-portfolio-reset-11772091609678.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-26T13:23:44","source":"Livemint"},{"id":"508799","title":"Sun Pharma's FY25 revenue reached Rs 520 Bn, with India contributing 33% and US formulations 31%. EBITDA margin improved to 29%.\nThe company operates in over 100 countries, leads the Indian pharma market with 8.4% share, and invests 6.2% of sales in R&D.","summary":"Sun Pharma's FY25 revenue reached Rs 520 Bn, with India contributing 33% and US formulations 31%. EBITDA margin improved to 29%.\nThe company operates in over 100 countries, leads the Indian pharma market with 8.4% share, and invests 6.2% of sales in R&D.","url":"https://www.bseindia.com/stockinfo/AnnPdfOpen.aspx?Pname=8ef19f3e-b9ef-4842-9ad9-d0b0120afe72.pdf","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-24T15:45:54","source":"BSE"},{"id":"508270","title":"Global PE firms like General Atlantic and KKR are exploring a $150-200M investment in Synthimed Labs, valuing it at $1B ahead of its IPO.\nSynthimed, backed by IndiaRF, specializes in APIs with 86% export revenue. Intense competition includes Sun Pharma, Cipla, and Dr. Reddy's.","summary":"Global PE firms like General Atlantic and KKR are exploring a $150-200M investment in Synthimed Labs, valuing it at $1B ahead of its IPO.\nSynthimed, backed by IndiaRF, specializes in APIs with 86% export revenue. Intense competition includes Sun Pharma, Cipla, and Dr. Reddy's.","url":"https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/global-pe-firms-line-up-for-indiarf-s-synthimed-labs-in-150-200-million-deal-11771898888381.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-24